# Project Structure Guide

This project follows a simple, maintainable structure for a Python-based AI newsletter system.

## Core Files
- Main entry point: [src/main.py](mdc:src/main.py)
- Configuration: [src/config.py](mdc:src/config.py)
- Type definitions: [src/types.py](mdc:src/types.py)

## Deployment
- Deployment script: [scripts/deploy.sh](mdc:scripts/deploy.sh)

## Configuration Files
- Environment variables template: [.env.example](mdc:.env.example)
- Python dependencies: [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt)

## Directory Structure
```
.
├── src/           # Source code
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── main.py    # Main application
│   ├── config.py  # Configuration
│   └── types.py   # Type definitions
├── scripts/       # Deployment and utility scripts
├── tests/         # Unit tests
│   └── __init__.py
├── .env           # Environment variables (not in repo)
├── requirements.txt # Python dependencies
└── README.md      # Project documentation
```
